        <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>C++ is underrated for ML</h3>
          <p>
            All four A* Island models (sim, CNN, MLP, bucket) are pure C++17 with zero dependencies.
            Compiles in seconds, runs fast, full control. No PyTorch, no CUDA — just math.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Calibration matters more than architecture</h3>
          <p>
            CMA-ES parameter optimization on the simulator gave bigger gains than switching model architectures.
            The R9 score of 90.9 was mostly calibration, not model complexity.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Query observations are gold</h3>
          <p>
            Using 50 queries to observe actual simulation outcomes, then Nelder-Mead tuning per-round
            gave +19 points on hard rounds. Real data beats priors.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Ensemble &gt; single model</h3>
          <p>
            Different models excel at different terrain classes. The optimal blend uses bucket for empty,
            sim for ports, CNN for mountains, and sim+MLP for settlements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
